The German born anti-apartheid activist has died at the age of 88. JOHANNESBURG - Beata Lipman, the woman famous for hand-writing the original Freedom Charter, has died at the age of 88. Her daughter Jane says Lipman died on Thursday after being ill for some time. The anti-apartheid activist, who was born in Germany, arrived in South Africa at a young age when her parents fled from the Nazi regime. #BeataLipman The ANC says its saddened by the news of Lipman&#39;s passing and has described her as a revolutionary democrat.ZNHer daughter says she ll be sorely missed: It s old age, she was 88 and had sustained some burns from water. She had spent about three months in ICU before being admitted to rehab. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)